The Mammoth Book of True Crime
by Colin Wilson

Interesting and often gruesome. The book is divided alphabetically into sections that reflect various aspects of crime.

Over 70 chapters, with subjects such as arson, assassination, blackmail, con men, headless corpses, mass murder, serial killers and suicide.
